The Hawks are raiding the offices of North West premier Supra Mahumapelo, News24 reported on Thursday. Reports by City Press in February stated that Mahumapelo was in the crosshairs of the state-capture investigation, after it emerged that he authorised a trip for senior North West health officials to India that was paid for by a Gupta-linked company. BREAKING: The Hawks are raiding the offices of North West Premier Supra Mahumapelo. Story by @J_chabalala via @News24 https://t.co/spAQHd1uKz  "We are currently at the offices of the premier. We are investigating a case of alleged corruption and fraud within the premier's office," Hawks regional spokesperson, Captain Tlangelani Rikhotso told News24. Following the February reports, Mahumapelo had announced that he would subject himself to a lifestyle audit. This is a developing story.